00:00:38.383 --> 00:00:42.841
 Which, when heated, evaporates into vapor, a gas. 

00:00:42.841 --> 00:00:46.298
 Constant heating of the steam when the temperature is high enough 

00:00:46.298 --> 00:00:49.550
 This caused the separation of water molecules 

00:00:49.550 --> 00:00:53.879
 Into hydrogen and oxygen atoms that roam freely. 

00:00:53.879 --> 00:00:57.352
 With a little more heat, the ionization process occurs 

00:00:57.352 --> 00:01:00.849
 The negatively charged electrons evade the atoms, 

00:01:00.849 --> 00:01:04.423
 Leaving behind positive ions. 

00:01:04.423 --> 00:01:09.783
 This mixture of positive and negative charges that freely circulate is plasma, 

00:01:09.783 --> 00:01:14.752
 At a sufficiently high temperature, any gas can be converted into a plasma. 

00:01:14.752 --> 00:01:18.772
 These charged particles that move freely behave very differently 

00:01:18.772 --> 00:01:21.565
 Of particles in other types of this substance. 

00:01:21.565 --> 00:01:25.263
 When the knob, solid, contains static electricity in it, 

00:01:25.263 --> 00:01:28.125
